# Core standards

- Never commit secrets, API keys, tokens, or production credentials. Use environment variables and secret managers; keep `.env` out of git.
- Prefer small, reviewable changes. AI-generated code must be reviewed like any other code.
- Match existing project layout, naming, and patterns before introducing new abstractions.
- Document non-obvious behavior in code or module docstrings; avoid redundant comments on obvious lines.
